13/08/2003
ZVORNIK, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Sulejman Tihic, a member of the BiH presidency, urged authorities in Republika Srpska (RS) to speed up efforts to locate mass graves.
During a visit Tuesday (12 August) to the Crni Vrh mass grave near Zvornik, he said that former RS authorities were responsible for a series of crimes in the area that "systematically involved dozens if not hundreds of people".
He noted that 35 mass graves found so far in the entity contained the remains of 6,000 victims.
(SRNA, HINA, BBC - 12/08/03)
